handbook-item-shield: Hold Sneak (<hk>sneak</hk>) to actively use the shield for blocking.
handbook-item-raft:
- Place the raft with a rightmouse click.
- rightmouse click on the raft to board it.
- With an oar in your active hotbar slot, you can move the raft.
- Disembark from the raft using the shift key.
- Pick up the raft using the shift button combined with a rightmouse click.
handbook-item-leaves: leaf blocks have a smaller chance to drop sticks and seeds than branchy leaf blocks. The chance is unaffected by tool used to harvest them. Unlike branchy leaf blocks, regular leaves will notcount against axe durability when cutting down a tree.
handbook-item-leavesbranchy: Branchy leaves are guaranteed to drop a stick. They also have a higher chance to drop seeds. The chance is unaffected by tool used to harvest them. Unlike normal leaf blocks, branchy leaves willcount against axe durability when cutting down a tree, if still connected to the trunk.
handbook-item-resinouslog: Resinous logs only generate in trees created at world generation. Never in trees that are grown from saplings. Such logs are not common, and only a small percentage of pines will have one.
handbook-item-poultice: Poultices are a sort of combination of bandage with other healing components, used to help heal wounds.
handbook-item-treeseed: Tree seed drop chance is unaffected by tool used to harvest the leaf block, however, if you fell an entire tree with an axe you will get far fewer seeds than if you had broken the leaf blocks first. Branchy leaves have a higher chance to drop seeds, compared to normal leaf blocks.
handbook-item-crate: Place in the crafting grid to open or close the crate. Combine with a parchment to be able to draw the crates current contents, use any pigment item to draw, for example charcoal.
handbook-item-stump: These tree remains are frequently found in nature and are not created by chopping down trees. They can be used for decoration or turned into regular logs with a little bit of trimming. They also are a great substrate forchlorociboria fungus that will dye the wood teal over time.
handbook-item-canes: Flexible canes drop from foliage blocks of certain trees: branchy leaf blocks have more chances to drop them than regular ones. Used to weave baskets and wattle fences.
handbook-item-leaf: Piles of leaves drop from foliage blocks of certain trees: regular leaf blocks have more chances to drop them than branchy ones. Any leaves can be an emergency food source, but some have more unique uses.
